<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France, U.S. Win in World Bridge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAMAMET, Tunisia, November 1 (Xinhua) -- Defending champions
both France and the United States beat their rivals to take the
Bermuda Bowl Cup and the Venice Cup for women at the world team
bridge championships on Friday.
</P>
<P>
In the Bermuda Bowl, open to both sexes, France overturned a
slim overnight deficit to lead the Americans by 279 points to 219
with the last 32 boards, a quarter of the match, to be played on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The two teams have shared the honors since 1994, with France
winning their first encounter three years ago in the final, and
claiming the title again in 1996. In 1995 the United States beat
the French in the semifinals.
</P>
<P>
The Venice Cup saw a 249-184 win for the American women.
</P>
<P>
For China, however, snatching second is the first time in its
10-year history in the world championships.
</P>
<P>
The best mark the Chinese women had made before was a third in
1991. 
</P>
</TEXT>
