<HEADLINE> Sampras Advances to Finals in Paris Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, November 1 (Xinhua) -- Pete Sampras overcame shoulder
problem to advance into the final of the Paris Indoor Open on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The world No.1 of the United States defeated Yevgeny Kafelnikov
of Russia, 7-6 (7-2), 6-3, to set up a meeting with either
Defending champion Thomas Enqvist or another Swedish Jonas
Bjorkman.
</P>
<P>
Sampras, one of the best tennis players ever in history, has
already claimed a berth in the ATP Tour World Championships in ten
days, while Kafelnikov could only rest his hope in Moscow to make
the eight-player field.
</P>
<P>
Sampras foght back from 5-4 dificit after he dropped his serve
to win a tiebreak in the first set.
</P>
<P>
He broke three times in the second set to make his seven finals
of the year with a 100-percent record in previous matches. 
</P>
</TEXT>
