<HEADLINE> Azevedo Successes in President Campaign of Benfica </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, November 1 (Xinhua) -- Lisbon lawyer Joao Vale Azevedo
beat won the president campaign of the Purtugal soccer giants club
Benfica Saturday.
</P>
<P>
In the month-lasting contest, Azevedo took 51.5 percent in
balloting.
</P>
<P>
The election victory ensured Scotsman Graeme Souness' coaching
in the Lisbon club, a promise of each candidate.
</P>
<P>
Benfica trailed League leader FC Porto 10 points with a ninth
place in the standings, plus debts of 38 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
