<HEADLINE> Arafat Chairs Committee Meeting Prior Washington </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, November 1 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian National
Authority (PNA) Chairman Yasser Arafat held the PNA Steering
Committee meeting today in Gaza to map out PNA's stand for the
upcoming Washington peace talks, Israel Radio said.
</P>
<P>
The committee briefed Arafat its preparations for the
Washington talks and Arafat gave specific instructions which will
guide the PNA delegation in its talks with the Israeli side in
Washington, but no details of the meeting and Arafat's
instructions were disclosed.
</P>
<P>
Arafat said in Gaza on Friday that he supports the upcoming
Washington peace talks between the Palestinians and Israelis, but
there will be no final-status talks unless Israeli troops being
redeployed first in West Bank and Gaza Strip under the Oslo
Agreement signed by the two sides.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Israeli Foreign Minister David Levy was quoted by
the Israel Radio as saying today that he was satisfied with
the negotiating principles formulated by the Israeli inner cabinet
and some progress could be made during the Washington talks.
</P>
<P>
Levy is scheduled to leave this evening for Washington as
head of the Israeli delegation to the Washington peace talks
which will be started on Monday.
</P>
<P>
He will discuss, among other issues, the Jewish settlement
and Israeli troop redeployment in the Palestinian territories with
PNA negotiator Abu Mazen, with the participation of U.S.
Secretary of State Madeleine Albright and U.S. Middle East
Peace Envoy Dennis Ross. 
</P>
</TEXT>
