<HEADLINE> Perot to Speak at Reform Party Convention </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, November 1 (Xinhua) -- Ross Perot is scheduled to
address the Reform Party Convention going on in Kansas City, in
the Midwest of the United States.
</P>
<P>
To earn official status, the Reform Party needs to complete a
platform and a constitution, and elect national officers. Most of
the events, which involve some 800 people from 47 states, are
being held at the Convention Center and the Marriott Hotel.
</P>
<P>
Perot, a Texas billionaire, got only 8.5 percent of the
presidential vote in 1996 down from 19 percent of the vote in
1992.
</P>
<P>
The Reform Party's National Founding Convention opened Friday
amid the hope by some that the party produce a battle in coming up
with a candidate for the 2000 presidential election, news reports
said.
</P>
<P>
Perot was virtually unopposed in gaining the party's nomination
in 1992 and 1996. He has yet to declare whether he will seek a
third nomination.
</P>
<P>
A number of dissatisfied party members branched off last year
to form the American Reform Party, complaining Perot was
subjecting the party to his unbending will and ideas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
