<HEADLINE> Pak President Meets with PLA Naval Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, November 1 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's President Farooq
Leghari said here today the on-going visit of Chinese President
Jiang Zeming to the United States is of great importance and the
Pakistani Government pays great attention to it.
</P>
<P>
Meeting with the visiting naval delegation of the Chinese
People's Liberation Army (PLA) led by Vice Admiral Shi Yunsheng,
Leghari stressed that Pakistan and China enjoy very good relations
which have stood the test of time.
</P>
<P>
recalling his meetings with Chinese President Jiang Zeming in
the recent years, Leghari said that the new generation of the
Chinese leadership with President Jiang in the core has the
foresight and sagacity.
</P>
<P>
Shi Yunsheng said on the occasion that China and Pakistan are
the two great neighbors, their friendship goes back ancient times.
</P>
<P>
The friendly and cooperative relationship, based on the Five
Principles of Peaceful Co-existence, has become a model among the
countries with different social systems, said Shi Yunsheng.
</P>
<P>
After the meeting, the president awarded "Sitar-e-Imtiaz"
(Distinction Star) to Shi Yunsheng in recognition of his
contributions in strengthening the friendship between the navies
of the two countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
