<HEADLINE> Mubarak: Israel Aborts U.S. Efforts For Peace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, November 1 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian President Hosni
Mubarak said here today that the United States is doing all
it can to advance the stalled peace process, but its efforts
had been aborted by an incorrigibly obstinate Israel.
</P>
<P>
In an exclusive interview with the UAE TV, Mubarak
said that as an important partner of the Middle East peace
process, the U.S. is "doing all it can (to promote the peace
process)."
</P>
<P>
"U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright went to Israel
and she told them the land-for-peace principle ... and this means
there are U.S. efforts to resolve (Israeli-Arab disputes)," he
said before he left the Gulf country today after a two-day
visit.
</P>
<P>
However, Mubarak said the U.S. efforts failed to yield any
results until now due to Israel's obstinacy in the peace process.
</P>
<P>
He warned that such Israeli stand will damage the peace
process and the deadlock in the Arab-Israeli peace talks will
lead to unstability in the region and the continuous violence in
many areas in the Arab and Israeli world against countries
related to peace.
</P>
<P>
The Middle East peace process was stalled after Israel
decided in February to build Jewish neighborhoods in Arab East
Jerusalem which Palestinians want to be the capital of a future
state. 
</P>
</TEXT>
