<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Palestinian Students Hold Anti-Israeli Demonstration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, November 1 (Xinhua) -- About 15,00 radical
Palestinian university students held an anti-Israeli rally today
in the West Bank city Nablus, calling for further confrontation
with Israel.
</P>
<P>
The demonstration was held by supporters of the militant group
Islamic Jihad to mark the second anniversary of the death of the
group's head Fathi Shakaki, who was murdered in Malta by Israeli
agents.
</P>
<P>
The students burned Israeli and American flags and chanted
anti-Israeli and anti-American slogans. Speakers in the rally
repeatedly called for more terror attacks against Israel.
</P>
<P>
Ramadan Shalah, leader of Islamic Jihad, spoke to the
demonstrators through telephone, urging them to continue the path
of confrontation and the Jihad (holy war) against Israel.
</P>
<P>
Islamic Jihad is the one of the two leading militant
anti-Israeli groups, together with the most famous Islamic
Resistance Movement (Hamas), which have been engaged in launching
suicide bombing attacks against Israeli targets.
</P>
<P>
The organization suffered a fatal blow early last year in
a major crackdown launched by the Palestinian National Authority
(PNA) following a wave of suicide attacks on Israeli buses
perpetrated by it and Hamas, killing 62 people and wounding
hundreds of others.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of its activists were detained and put into jails
by the PNA under the Israeli pressure. Since then, Islamic
Jihad has not launched major terror attacks against Israel.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971102.0022 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Calls for Promotion of Understanding Between China, U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOSTON, November 1 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese President Jiang
Zemin today called for the promotion of mutual understanding
between China and the United States.
</P>
<P>
Delivering a speech at Harvard University, Jiang said that
mutual understanding is the basis for state-to-state relations.
</P>
<P>
"Without it, it would be impossible for countries to build
trust and promote cooperation with each other," he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said since the establishment of diplomatic ties between
China and the United States, mutual understanding between the
Chinese and American peoples have broadened and developed steadily.
</P>
<P>
"However, this is not enough," the Chinese president said. "To
promote the development of China-U.S. relations, China needs to
know the United States better and vice versa."
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that to know China better, it is important to
approach China from a historical and cultural perspective. He
shared his four observations on the Chinese tradition with his
American audience, in a bid to help them know China better.
</P>
<P>
He said the Chinese people have the tradition of solidarity and
unity, of maintaining independence, of peace-loving and of
constantly striving for self perfection.
</P>
<P>
On the tradition of solidarity and unity, Jiang said: "Since
the time immemorial, people of all nationalities have established
closely-knitted political, economic and cultural links and joined
hands in developing the vast land of our country."
</P>
<P>
He said China became a vast unified country more than 2,000
years ago. Solidarity and unity have been inscribed in the hearts
of the Chinese people as part of their national identity.
</P>
<P>
"Despite occasional division in the Chinese history, ethnic
harmony and national unity have remained the main stream in the
history of the Chinese nation, and an important guarantee for
China's development and progress," he noted.
</P>
<P>
Since the founding of the People's Republic of China, a new
type of relationship of equality, solidarity and mutual assistance
between the 56 Chinese nationalities has been established, he said.
</P>
<P>
"People of all nationalities enjoy full rights and freedoms
provided for by the law, and in places where there is a high
concentration of minority nationality people, regional autonomy is
in practice," he added.
</P>
<P>
On the tradition of maintaining independence, Jiang said: "Our
ancestors always regarded the spirit of maintaining independence
as the foundation of a nation."
</P>
<P>
In modern times, the frequent bullying and humiliation by
imperialist powers once weakened China. However, after a hundred
years' struggle of the entire Chinese nation, China has stood up
again as a giant, he said.
</P>
<P>
"Today, in finding a road to development suited to us, we
will proceed from our own national conditions" instead from
"copying other countries' models," he noted.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the tradition of peace-loving, the Chinese
president said Chinese thinkers living more than 2,000 years ago
advanced the doctrine "loving people and treating neighbors
kindly are most valuable to a country."
</P>
<P>
"This is a reflection of the aspiration of the Chinese
people for a peaceful world where people of all countries live in
harmony," he said.
</P>
<P>
Today, the Chinese people who are committed to modernization
need more than ever a long-term international environment of peace
and a favorable neighboring environment, he said.
</P>
<P>
China's foreign policy is peace-oriented, he said.
</P>
<P>
"We will establish and develop friendly relations and
cooperation with all countries in the world on the basis of the
Five Principles of Peaceful Coexistence," he noted.
</P>
<P>
A developing and progressing China does not pose a threat to
anyone, and will never seek hegemony even if it is developed in
the future, he said.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the tradition of constantly striving for
self-perfection, Jiang said the fruits of China's ancient
civilization were brought about by the tireless efforts and hard
work of the Chinese nation.
</P>
<P>
"Under the guidance of Mao Zedong Thought, the Chinese
Communist Party led the Chinese people in achieving China's
national independence and people's liberation and in building
China into a socialist country with initial prosperity," he said.
</P>
<P>
"Today, guided by Deng Xiaoping Theory, the Chinese people are
firmly pressing ahead with reform and opening-up and have made
remarkable achievements in the modernization drive," he added.
</P>
<P>
China has entered a period with the fastest and healthiest
development in this century, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
The friendly exchanges between the Chinese and American peoples
date back to more than 200 years ago, he said. Many Chinese
contributed to the nation-building of the United States, while a
lot of American friends helped and supported the national
liberation cause of the Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
"In our course to further open up and achieve modernization, we
have spared no efforts in learning from all the fine cultural
achievements of the American people," he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang spoke highly of Harvard University's efforts on China
studies and presented the school with a set of newly published
Twenty-Four Histories with Mao Zedong's Comments. Twenty-Four
Histories are important classical works on China's history of
thousands of years.
</P>
<P>
Jiang is on a nine-day tour of the United States, the first by
a Chinese head of state to the United States in 12 years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971102.0023 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-01 17:42 </DATE_TIME>
