<HEADLINE> Strange Snake With Claws Killed in Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, November 1 (Xinhua) -- A strange colorful snake with
two claws was found and killed in Iran's northeastern province of
Khorasan.
</P>
<P>
Local Persian-language daily "Kayhan" reported today that the
snake attacked two surveyors when they were working near a village
25 kilometers away from the provincial capital of Mashhad.
</P>
<P>
One of the surveyors said that the snake suddenly jumped down
from a three, stood on its two claws and then attacked him and his
colleague. The two were forced to use stone and stick to kill the
snake, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The snake had beautiful colors, two claws and five teeth in
its mouth, the daily said, adding that its length was about 120
centimeters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
