<HEADLINE> Floods Kill 57 People in Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, November 1 (Xinhua) -- Floods caused by
overflowing rivers in Afder and Liben districts of Ethiopia's
Somali Region have killed 57 people and besieged thousands of
others, the Ethiopian News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The report said thousands of people in the area are surrounded
by the water, indicating that the problem is acute, particularly
in Dollo Addo town.
</P>
<P>
Over 4,000 people have been displaced while 9,045 domestic
animals and vegetables grown on 655 hectares of land were washed
away, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, floods caused by heavy downpour in three rural
districts of the region have also washed away 80 pet animals and
destroyed 90 houses.
</P>
<P>
Unspecified amount of property has been destroyed while 15
people sustained heavy and light injuries, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The Dire Dawa Administration Disaster Prevention and
Preparedness Office has expressed readiness to provide the
victims with emergency ration, the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
