<HEADLINE> Iran Calls for Cooperation to Solve Caspian Sea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, November 1 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Foreign Minister Kamal
Kharrazi called here today for cooperation among the Caspian Sea
littoral states to determine the legal status of the sea.
</P>
<P>
He made the call in a meeting with visiting Kazakh deputy
Foreign Minister Erlan Edrisov.
</P>
<P>
Kharrazi expressed Iran's insistence that until the legal
status of the Caspian Sea is determined, none of the five littoral
countries has the right to take unilateral measures to explore the
resources of the sea.
</P>
<P>
Edrisov said in the meeting that the Caspian Sea belongs to the
five littoral states, and all issues concerning the sea should be
settled unanimously.
</P>
<P>
The five littoral countries of the Caspian Sea are Iran,
Kazakhstan, Russia, Turkmenistan and Azerbaijan.
</P>
<P>
The Caspian Sea issue has emerged after some of the Caspian
states have signed agreements with foreign countries to explore
oil reserves in the world's biggest inland sea.
</P>
<P>
Experts said that the Caspian Sea has rich oil and gas reserves
which may turn the region into another arena of oil-producing
competition after the Persian Gulf and even political
confrontation.
</P>
<P>
Edrisov arrived here today to exchange views on bilateral
relations with Iranian officials and to explore ways for
cooperation between the two countries in oil and gas sector.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
