<HEADLINE> Young Couple Linked by Yangtze, Yellow River Water Control Projects  (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANDOUPING (Three Gorges), November 2 (Xinhua) -- Cao Weiguo
and Liu Shujin, an ordinary couple in their mid 30s, have been
working respectively on China's two largest rivers.
</P>
<P>
Thirty-four-year-old Cao is a driver on the worksite here of
the Three Gorges Project, a gigantic project under construction on
China's largest Yangtze River, only next to the Great Wall built
more than two millennia ago, while his wife Liu Shujin, 35, is a
tunnel and culvert engineer for Xiaolangdi Water Control project,
the biggest on the Yellow River. Both rivers are renowed to have
nurtured and nourished the Chinese civilization.
</P>
<P>
The young couple, who are admired and often on the lips of
fellow workers or technicians at their respective worksites, have
become the most sought-after figures by journalists, who flocked
to Sandouping and Xiaolangdi to cover them.
</P>
<P>
On the morning of October 28, when the gap of the Xiaolangdi
dam was joined up, Cao learned from his workmates that his wife
was appearing in a live-cast TV program on the daming process by
China Central Television. Just coming off the night shift, he
hurried back to his dormitory.
</P>
<P>
To his disappointment, Cao missed the shots showing his wife
and, in the evening, he made a phone call to her and told her of
his regret at not seeing her on TV.
</P>
<P>
Incidently, that day happened to be the birthday of their
nine-year old daughter Wenwen. Cao then dialed his wife's home,
where they had sent their daughter years ago, and shared with the
girl the joy of seeing her mother on TV.
</P>
<P>
"Not everybody is as lucky as us, as we have been working on
our country's two largest water hydro-power projects." said Liu,
adding that "both of us are filled with pride in spite of the
hardships and arduous jobs we working on."
</P>
<P>
It chanced that they met over ten years ago when both worked at
the construction site of Ankang Hydropower Station in southwest
China's Sichuan province.
</P>
<P>
One evening, upon hearing that Liu's quilt was too thin to keep
warm, Cao Weiguo climbed over the mountains that kept them apart
and sent his own quilt to his sweetheart.
</P>
<P>
Afterwards, they fell in love and did not hesitate to let
others know.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971102.0068 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Young Couple Linked by Yangtze, Yellow River Water Control Projects  (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"What I like of him is that he is so affectionate and care for
me meticulously," said Liu, and she had a deft hand and a lively
character that also attracted him too. Both agreed, she added, and
"what brought us together at the very first is our common career."
</P>
<P>
And they both have sacrificed much for their career. For the
sake of building the two mammoth water control projects, the
couple has met only once annually over the past four years.
</P>
<P>
Thirsty for a family union, Cao once urged his wife to retire
earlier or to find herself anther job. And it was his father, a
water conservation veteran worker who encouraged them to stay on
their jobs and continue to contribute their share to the cause of
the country's water conservation and power generation.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the rapid progress made in the two projects
convinced Cao and his wife and gradually changed their mind.
"Every step forward taken in construction of the projects enable
us to feel our effort worthwhile," he said.
</P>
<P>
Cao Weiguo has made three trips to his wife's worksite in
recent years and, during each trip he felt inspired by her hard
work. But he also has some worries for her health, as he saw Liu
working for long hours each day in the water diversion tunnel
filled with dirt and amid roaring of machines.
</P>
<P>
Liu came to the Three Gorges last September. Seeing the
activities seething with enthusiasm at the construction site, she
couldn't but gasp with admiration at the massive constructions and
felt more proud of her husband.
</P>
<P>
As they live far apart in three places, the couple and their
lively daughter ofter miss one another. "My best pastime, more
than playing basketball and listening to music, is looking at the
photo album of my wife and daughter."
</P>
<P>
When their nine-year-old Wenwen talks to her young pals, she
often said with a sense of pride, "my dad and mum are just great.
One is at the Three Gorges, and the other in Xiaolangdi." 
</P>
