<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Air Force Destroys Tamil Rebel Ship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, November 2 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan Air Force
destroyed a Tamil rebel supply ship carrying a consignment of
weapons en route to the northeastern coastal city of Mullaitivu
early this morning, the state-owned radio station said today.
</P>
<P>
Air Force Chief Oliver Ranasinghe was quoted by the station as
saying that the ship was completely destroyed near Mullaitivu
early today. Another radio station TNL said the ship was sunken.
</P>
<P>
He said the rebels of the Liberation of Tigers of Tamil Eelam
(LTTE) were about to unload the weapons from the anchored ship at
the time of the attack.
</P>
<P>
The chief commander described the result of the attack as one
of the greatest achievements of the troops.
</P>
<P>
But it's still unknown how many weapons and what kinds of
weapons were on board the sunken ship. Immediate casualty of the
fighting is also yet to know.
</P>
<P>
The Air Force also destroyed several boats rushed to their
ill-fated ship for reinforcement, it was said.
The LTTE has been fighting for a separate state of their own in
the north and east of the country since 1983.  
</P>
