<HEADLINE> CCPIT to Better Serve China's Foreign Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 2 (Xinhua) -- The China Council for the
Promotion of International Trade (CCPIT) expects to contribute
more to China's foreign trade strategy, said new CCPIT President
Yu Xiaosong.
</P>
<P>
CCPIT should be committed to promoting the entry of Chinese
businesses into the world market, furthering international trade
and introducing advanced foreign technology and investment into
China, he said in an interview.
</P>
<P>
As an non-governmental trade-promotion organization, CCPIT has
played the role of intermediary by offering services to Chinese
businesses such as providing trade information, holding
exhibitions and carrying out business arbitration.
</P>
<P>
Yu, also president of the China Chamber of International
Commerce, said that the variety of China's foreign trade presented
CCPIT with both development opportunities and challenges.
</P>
<P>
In addition to 5,000 foreign trade companies, more than 6,000
businesses and 140,000 foreign-funded enterprises have been
granted the authority to handle imports and exports, he
said. China will replace the present foreign trade examination and
approval system with a new foreign trade registration system by
the end of 2000. CCPIT should then be able to establish ties with
all kinds of businesses.
</P>
<P>
Two major priorities for CCPIT, he said, are service to central
and western China and to small and medium-sized enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Last year, CCPIT helped the Ningxia Hui Automonous Region in
northwestern China hold trade fairs abroad with good results, Yu
said.
</P>
<P>
He said China will not only further trade with its traditional
partners such as the European Union, the United States and Japan,
but will also advance economic exchanges with South America and
Africa. CCPIT should be more active in promoting China's economic
and trade relations with South America and Africa.
</P>
<P>
CCPIT will hold Chinese commodity fairs in Panama and South
Africa later this month, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
