<HEADLINE> Ding Guangen on Promoting Ethical and Cultural Progress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, November 2 (Xinhua) -- Top Chinese propaganda official
Ding Guangen said popularizing the guidelines of the Party's 15th
national congress should stress upholding the banner of Deng
Xiaoping Theory and advancing ethical and cultural progress.
</P>
<P>
Ding, head of the Propaganda Department of the CPC Central
Committee and member of the political bureau of the CPC Central
Committee, made his remarks during a recent inspection tour in
Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region in south China.
</P>
<P>
Advancing ethical and cultural progress must center on economic
construction and serve the fundamental goals of the whole Party
and the country, he said.
</P>
<P>
"Combining promoting ethical and cultural progress with
modernization construction, the former will produce a uniting
force which in turn stimulates productivity," Ding said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that promoting moral progress should proceed from
the reality that China is now at the primary stage of
socialism. "Therefore we should be very practical in making plans
and setting goals," he said.
</P>
<P>
Ding said the key to promoting ethical and cultural progress
lies in intensifying moral and ideological education, especially
among young people.
</P>
<P>
He called on government officials to concern themselves with
the well-being of the people and do everything in their interests
and solve their problems.
</P>
<P>
"We should make sure that promoting ethical and cultural
progress win the consent and support of our people," Ding
said. 
</P>
