<HEADLINE> Philippine Government to Strengthen Anti-Graft Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, November 2 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos
today vowed to pursue with greater vigor the campaign against
graft and corruption in the government during the remaining eight
months of his term.
</P>
<P>
He said his objective is to institutionalize effective,
preventive, and punitive measures to curb graft and corruption in
the government as one of his lasting legacies to the Filipino
people.
</P>
<P>
"I would like to leave behind a bureaucracy with unquestioned
integrity, efficiency and credibility," he said.
</P>
<P>
Ramos reaffirmed his commitment to clean, honest and efficient
governance after receiving an updated report on his
administration's anti-graft and corruption campaign from the
Presidential Management Staff.
</P>
<P>
The report said that so far this year, various government
agencies have disposed thousands of graft and corruption cases,
most of which are minor offenses.
</P>
<P>
About 300 people including prosecutors, regional directors and
government employees have been dismissed from office or sentenced
to jail for these offenses, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this year, Ramos ordered all heads of government
agencies to submit a regular report on the implementation of
various measures the government introduced to curb graft and
corruption in their respective offices.
</P>
<P>
Ramos has vowed that he would not seek re-election as his term
of office expires on June 30 next year.  
</P>
