<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Farmers Build New Home before River Blockage (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANDOUPING (Three Gorges), November 2 (Xinhua) -- Zheng
Bangzhou, a young farmer living beside the Yangtze in the Three
Gorges area, finds it hard to believe that within two and a half
months, his family moved from a simple adobe house into a new
two-story 160-sq m building.
</P>
<P>
Zheng and his family in Quxi village of Zigui County are among
the 39,600 people to be resettled before the flood season sets in
next May, when their present homes will be submerged by the river
as a result of its damming on the coming Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The river blocking will signal the completion of the
first-phase of the Three Gorges Project, the world's largest water
control undertaking.
</P>
<P>
To compensate for Zheng's 116-sq-m house and 0.15-ha cropland,
the government paid 15,000 yuan. With the compensation and their
own savings totaling more than 20,000 yuan, the 30-year-old farmer
and his wife have had built the new house and opened a tailor's
shop by the highway.
</P>
<P>
By now, all the 135 residents in Zheng's village moved into new
homes, and the majority of the rest of the 39,600 people will be
relocated.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government attaches great importance to the
relocation of residents at the site of the Three Gorges reservoir,
which is crucial to the success of the massive project, as Premier
Li Peng emphasized repeatedly. The government has drafted an
initial budget of 40 billion yuan for (to be adjusted with
inflation) and 14 preferential policies to resettlement.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971102.0085 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Farmers Build New Home before River Blockage (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A comprehensive development-oriented resettlement program,
moreover, has been in the place of traditional compensation-only
scheme.
</P>
<P>
The Three Gorges reservoir area has been designated as a
national economic development zone, with Yichang, Wanxian, Fuling
and several other cities enjoying policies granted to coastal open
cities.
</P>
<P>
The central government also calls for 20 provinces and
municipalities and ten major and medium-sized cities to render
help to resettlement, and requires all the ministries and
commissions under the State Council to give priority to
resettlement when allocating development projects and funds.
</P>
<P>
In another development, the state helps the reservoir area to
introduce more overseas funds, and recently granted tax breaks to
import of materials and equipment by businesses registered in the
area.
</P>
<P>
Among others, the preferences include the recruitment of
workers for construction projects in and near the Three Gorges
area primarily from the areas to be submerged by the Three Gorges
Project; granting of tax breaks to land development and
businesses launched by resettled farmers, and contribution of a
certain proportion of revenues from power generation by the
project to the resettlement fund.
</P>
<P>
The Three Gorges Project, initiated in December 1993 and
striding Hubei province and Chongqing municipality in central and
southwestern China, will submerged 6.32 million sq km of land, and
the population to be relocated is expected to hit 1.2 million
eventually.  
</P>
</TEXT>
