<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 2 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong police arrested 10
Vietnamese after seizing 63 kilograms of suspected cannabis
Saturday in an operation against drug trafficking, a police report
said today.
</P>
<P>
Acting on tip-offs, the police stopped three men Saturday
afternoon in Ferry Street, Kowloon, and in a subsequent search
found they possessed about 10 kilograms of suspected cannabis.
</P>
<P>
Follow-up inquiries led to a further seizure of 53 kilograms of
suspected cannabis in a flat in the street. Seven persons inside
the flat were arrested.
</P>
<P>
All the 10 people arrested in the operation are identified as
Vietnamese.
</P>
<P>
The seizure can fetch a market value of about four million HK
dollars (512,820 U.S. dollars). The arrested, aged between 21 and
37, are still being detained for further inquires.  
