<HEADLINE> Major Economic Briefs from Mercosur </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, November 1 (Xinhua) -- Following are major briefs
from the Southern Common Market (Mercosur).
</P>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO -- Industry ministers of Mercosur member countries
signed agreements here on Tuesday on further promoting the trade
of industrial products inside the bloc under fair competition.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was forged during the first meeting of Mercosur
industry ministers, who discussed issues such as the juridical
framework for the association of enterprises, the integration
committees between departments, states and provinces.
</P>
<P>
The ministers agreed to focus more on the quality of industrial
products and to coordinate certification systems in a bid to
strengthen competition in the markets outside the region.
</P>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO -- Mercosur countries decided to create
intergovernmental commissions to fight the dengue, hantavirus and
Chagas malady plaguing the region as well as emergency situation
caused by natural disasters.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made on October 29 during a meeting held in
Montevideo by Public Health ministers of Mercosur countries --
Argentina, Brazil, Paraguay, Uruguay and the regional bloc's
associated members of Bolivia and Chile.
</P>
<P>
GUANACASTE, Costa Rica -- Mercosur countries voiced
satisfaction over the results of the preparatory meeting for the
negotiations of the Free Trade Area of the Americas (FTAA) that
ended here on October 30.
</P>
<P>
Uruguayan Vice Foreign Minister Carlos Perez del Castillo said
on behalf of the Mercosur that the bloc's positions were accepted,
but some important themes are still pending. They are subject to
discussions starting next year.
</P>
<P>
The Mercosur also expressed special interest in bringing up the
agriculture theme, and backed Rio de Janeiro, of Brazil, as a
candidate for the site of the FTAA secretariat.
</P>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO -- Presidents of Mercosur countries will meet for
the 13th time on December 15 to discuss relations between the
Mercosur and the FTAA, said the Uruguayan provisional presidency.
</P>
<P>
The presidents will also try to finalize trade liberalization
agreements with Mexico, Venezuela and other Andean countries at
the summit.
</P>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO -- Mercosur countries and those of the Andean
Community failed at a three-day meeting starting October 29 to
prepare a free trade agreement scheduled for signing before the
end of the year.
</P>
<P>
Main obstacles include the definitions for the terms of tariff
exemptions and the drafting of a list of "sensitive" products
between the two blocs.
</P>
<P>
The Mercosur countries and Andean Community members decided to
restart their talks two weeks later in Lima, Peru.
</P>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO -- The Mercosur will start negotiations with Canada
on a juridical framework of economic cooperation, said Uruguayan
Foreign Minister Alvaro Ramos.
</P>
<P>
The minister, now on a visit to Canada, confirmed that there is
political interest on the part of Canada to approach the Mercosur.
</P>
<P>
"They have handed us a juridical framework project and we are
going to submit it to the consideration of the Mercosur organs to
arrive at a definitive common position on the matter," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
