<HEADLINE> Chinese President Arrives in Los Angeles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, November 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang
Zemin arrived in Los Angeles, California, this afternoon on the
last leg of his nine-day state visit to the United States.
</P>
<P>
Jiang flew in from Boston, Massachusetts, where he delivered a
speech at the famous Harvard University before winding up his tour
of the U.S. East.
</P>
<P>
Among those present at the Los Angeles International Airport to
greet the Chinese leader were Richard Riordan, mayor of Los
Angeles, Zev Yarolavsky, chairman of the Los Angeles County Board
of Supervisors, Lee Grissom, representative of California Governor
Pete Wilson, Fong Sheson, Chinese counsel general in Los Angeles,
and 200 representatives from the local Chinese community. Two
teenagers presented flowers to Jiang and his wife Wang Yeping.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in this largest city on the U.S. west coast,
Jiang is scheduled to meet privately with Governor Wilson and
Mayor Riordan, visit Hughes Electronics Corporation and have
contacts with business executives, Chinese community leaders and
other dignitaries on different occasions.
</P>
<P>
Accompanying Jiang were Chinese Vice-Premier and Foreign
Minister Qian Qichen, special assistant Zeng Qinghong, Director of
the Foreign Affairs of the State Council Liu Huaqiu, special
assistant Teng Wensheng and other senior government officials.
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles and California have close trade ties with
China. More than a quarter of the U.S. exports to China come from
California, and China currently ranks as California's sixth
largest foreign trade partner.
</P>
<P>
The China market, expected to grow rapidly, imports six billion
U.S. dollars worth of products annually from California, mostly
computers and aerospace equipment. So far this year, California's
exports to China have been up 20 percent, according to the state
Trade and Commerce Agency.
</P>
<P>
This is Jiang's first tour of Los Angeles, a city trying to be
the international trade center for the United States in the 21st
century. He visited San Francisco, also in California, when he was
mayor of Shanghai. 
</P>
</TEXT>
