<HEADLINE> Technological Boost for Three Gorges Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANDOUPING (Three Gorges), November 2 (Xinhua) -- Unparalleled
technical difficulties used to be a big headache for the ongoing
Three Gorges Project. In solving these difficulties,
high-technology has demonstrated its power.
</P>
<P>
The use of high technology not only saved 4 billion yuan (about
481.9 million U.S. dollars), but also expedited construction
during the past five years, said one project official. The project
so far has involved such a wide range of technological research
and science fields that it could be called a showcase of
high-technology.
</P>
<P>
The official said the project's technological research required
teamwork on an unprecedented scale in such areas as geology,
seismology, structural engineering, hydrology, flood control,
soils engineering, shipping power, mechanical and electrical
engineering, ecology and environmental engineering.
</P>
<P>
Even before the project began, feasibility studies were under
way for almost half a century, the official said, adding that
Chinese scientists have conducted more than 1,800 scientific
research projects during the past 10 years.
</P>
<P>
Although Three Gorges will generate 84.6 billion kilowatt-hours
of electricity a year, almost 6.5 times that of the existing
Gezhouba Power Plant, only 20 percent of the manpower required to
build Gezhouba was needed at Three Gorges. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
