<HEADLINE> d p s 1867 China-Three Gorges-Bidding New Bidding for Three Gorges Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANDOUPING (Three Gorges), November 2 (Xinhua) -- The Three
Gorges project is expected to purchase more equipment through
international bidding next year, according to a project official
today.
</P>
<P>
Cited as another big deal after the 730 million US
dollar-generator contract concluded last August, it will mainly
include transformers, high-voltage electrical equipment, and
equipment to be used in large-scale power plants, said Li Yong'an,
deputy manager of the China Yangtze Three Gorges Project
Development Corporation.
</P>
<P>
Li said that international commercial loans and export credit
will remain indispensable for the international businesses to win
the contract, and foreign government loans will be "especially
welcome".
</P>
<P>
As the world's largest comprehensive water control project, the
Three Gorges Project is open to bidding in its project
construction, equipment purchase, and management supervision,
according to a company official in charge of the planning for the
project bidding.
</P>
<P>
"We introduced competition mechanism from the very start of the
project, and adopted international conventional methods with
regard to selection of the construction teams and equipment
suppliers in line with 'open bidding, and fair competition and
evaluation'," said the official.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the project has signed more than 2,300
contracts by last July, with most of those involved in equipment
purchase won by foreign suppliers. Two European-led conglomerates
won the most lucrative contracts in August for the supply of 14
generators and turbines for the project.
</P>
<P>
Nevertheless, the damming of the Yange on November 8 will
result in an unparalleled amount of construction work, and even
more opportunities for international equipment suppliers, said the
official. 
</P>
</TEXT>
