<DOCNO> XIE19971102.0163 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Milestone of Three Gorges Project (6) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANDOUPING (Three Gorges), November 2 (Xinhua) -- The Yangtze
River, the world's third longest, is to be dammed on November 8,
signaling the end of the first-phase construction on the Three
Gorges Project.
</P>
<P>
The damming will block the main channel of the Yangtze River by
linking two parallel earth-and-stone cofferdams. The water after
the damming is to flow into the man-made diversion channel besides
the construction site.
</P>
<P>
Water and silt between the cofferdams will be removed and work
will begin on the huge dam and workshops to be built on the dried
up riverbed for the Three Gorges Hydropower Station.
</P>
<P>
One of the factors making the damming a difficult job is the
speed and volume of the water flow, experts said. Developers have
to resolve such enigmas as preventing the potential collapse of
the cofferdams and building leak-proof walls. The damming
constitutes not only a test to technologies related to the river
blocking but the first examinaktion on the overall engineering
design of the Three Gorges Project.
</P>
<P>
Rivers are usually dammed in dry season so that the flow is
at its lowest point, making it easier to close the cofferdams.
</P>
<P>
According to studies conducted in Yichang, the Hubei Province
city nearest the dam site, the Yangtze's lowest flow rate occurs
in late January to late February, a mere 2,950 cubic meters per
second to 6,100 cubic meters per second. To allow adequate time
for developers to build cofferdams to the projected height
required during peak water flow during flood season which begins
in May, engineers picked the November 8 as the date to block the
Yangtze. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971102.0164 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Text of Jiang's Speech at Harvard University (Part Eight) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The reform and opening-up endeavor is an embodiment and a
creative development of the Chinese spirit of constantly striving
for self-perfection and renovation in modern times. We refer to
our reform and opening-up as socialist reform and opening-up
because they constitute the process of self-improvement and
development of the socialist system in China. The practice in
recent twenty years has eloquently proved that we are right in
direction, firm in conviction, steady in our steps and gradual in
our approach when carrying out the reform and opening up and have
achieved tremendous successes. We have successfully overcome
various difficulties and risks in the course of our advance
without causing great social unrest. Rather, we have succeeded in
greatly releasing and developing productive forces and maintained
social stability and an all-round progress.
</P>
<P>
We are conducting a comprehensive reform with full
confidence. Economically, we will speed up the establishment of a
socialist market economy and realize industrialization, and the
socialization, marketization and modernization of the
economy. Politically, we will endeavor to develop socialist
democracy, govern the country according to law, build a socialist
country under the rule of law and ensure the full exercise of
people's rights to govern the country and manage social
affairs. Culturally, we will work hard to develop a scientific
socialist culture for the people, a culture that is geared to the
needs of modernization, of the nation, of the world and of the
future, adopt a strategy of rejuvenating China through science and
education, and strive to raise the political and moral standards as
well as scientific and cultural level of the entire nation. In a
word, it is to build our country into a prosperous, strong,
democratic and culturally advanced modern country.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971102.0165 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Text of Jiang's Speech at Harvard University (Part Nine) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
China, a country with vast territory, a big population and a
long history, should make greater contribution to humanity. The
Chinese people waged a dauntless struggle for one hundred
years. They have effected great reforms and changes one after
another to build China into a strong and prosperous country. They
have worked to strengthen ethnic harmony and achieve national
reunification and to promote the lofty cause of world peace and
development. In the final analysis, they have done all these for
one objective, that is the great rejuvenation of the Chinese
nation and China's greater contribution to humanity.
</P>
<P>
In short, the choice of the social system and development path
that China has made, the domestic and foreign policies that it has
pursued and the goals it has identified for the next century are
all based on both the reality and the history. Therefore, they are
not only in conformity with the trend of the historical
development of mankind and that of the times, but also reflect
the characteristics of the Chinese nation. They serve not only the
fundamental interests of the Chinese people, but also world peace,
stability, prosperity and progress. This is the key to an
understanding of the present China and its future.
</P>
</TEXT>
