<HEADLINE> Economy Booming in South China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANTOU, November 2 (Xinhua) -- The economy in Shantou city in
south China's Guangdong province, one of the country's leading
export centers, witnessed a notable increase in the first three
quarters of this year.
</P>
<P>
The city realized a gross domestic product of 26.14 billion
yuan (3.14 billion US dollars), up 15.3 percent over the same
period of last year.
</P>
<P>
During the period, its industrial sector scored 40.29 billion
yuan (4.85 billion US dollars) in added value, an increase of 25.3
percent on a yearly basis. Foreign trade went up by 57 percent
over last year to 5.2 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Shantou collected 2.2 billion yuan (265 million US dollars)
from revenue in the first nine months, up 22.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the city's GDP this year is expected to increase
by 16 percent to hit 37.5 billion yuan (4.5 billion US dollars).
</P>
</TEXT>
