<HEADLINE> Beijing-Taiwan Cultural Exchanges Flourish </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 2 (Xinhua) -- Numerous cultural exchange
activities have taken place between Beijing and Taiwan in recent
years.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese capital has sent 21 groups of 51 artists to visit
Taiwan in the past two years, and at the same time the
municipality has received six groups of 112 visitors in the circle
of art and culture from Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Over a dozen art forms were represented, including painting,
calligraphy, Peking Opera, acrobatics, puppetry, drama, music,
dance, and photography.
</P>
<P>
A number of Beijing's Peking Opera stars such as Mei Baojiu,
Zhao Baoxiu, and Wang Shufang, have visited Taiwan to perform or
lecture on Peking Opera, a 200-year old art form popular in both
Beijing and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
To date, more than 500 art students in Taiwan have attended
classes taught by teachers from the Beijing Opera
School. Meanwhile, many of the students have come to Beijing to
meet and work with young artists.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Taiwan will send 19 directors of culture centers
to Beijing to attend a series of discussions and meetings on the
development of cultural exchange between the two sides. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
