<HEADLINE> China's Jiangsu Province Diversifies Sources of Funding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, November 2 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangsu province
has successfully diversified its sources of funding for economic
growth, official figures indicate.
</P>
<P>
Besides fiscal allocations and bank loans, funds raised
directly from the capital market are becoming increasingly
important as a source of funding for enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Official data show that 34 enterprises in the eastern Chinese
province issued and listed shares by the end of June, raising 16.1
billion yuan in aggregate.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, direct and off-floor trading in property rights is
also gaining popularity in Jiangsu.
</P>
<P>
The diversification of funding has helped enterprises to
improve their operations and lower their asset-to-liability
ratios, a provincial official said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
