<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Book Fair Attracts Fans in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 2 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese capital recently
held its 16th book fair with discounted prices at the Beijing
Working People's Cultural Palace, attracting over 400,000 visitors.
</P>
<P>
Over 400 bookstores and publishing houses attended the 11-day
event, bringing some 150,000 titles of book, most of which were
twenty to thirty percent cheaper than the original price.
</P>
<P>
Most visitors agreed that the book fair offered them a good
chance to choose their favorites from a wide variety of works. The
event also saved them a lot of time by not having to travel around
to the many bookstores scattered throughout the city.
</P>
<P>
Literary works, children's stories, books on electronics and on
history, and dictionaries were the hottest items.
</P>
<P>
Total sales volume was more than 20 million yuan (about 2.5
million US dollars), figures show.
</P>
<P>
"Bookstores and publishing houses made considerable profits
from such a large-scale book fair, for the cheaper books attracted
bigger crowds of buyers than at any other time of the business
year," said an analyst from the publishing circle.  
</P>
</TEXT>
