<HEADLINE> Szeczenko Wins Women's Long Program in Nations Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, November 1 (Xinhua) -- The former German champion Tanja
Szewczenko performed with five triple jumps to win women's long
program in the Nations Cup figure skating competitons in
Gelsenkirchen, Germany on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Szewczenko lost steam in the last minute of her program,
doubling on a triple, singling on a double and hitting one double
axel in the music from the soundtrack "Speed".
</P>
<P>
The European champion Irina Slutskaya came to the second place
by hitting five triples in the choreographed program set to
Russian folk music.
</P>
<P>
Elena Liashenko of Urkaine followed in third with a classical
program set to Puccini, hitting five triples and botching a
landing on just one.
</P>
<P>
Two-time silver world medalists in ice dancing, Anjelika
Krylova and Oleg Ovsyannikov of Russia earned the highest score
with their "Carmen" in ice dancing.
</P>
<P>
Marina Anissina and Gwendal Peizerat of France finished second,
ahead of Irina Romanova and Igor Yaoshenko of Urkaine.
</P>
<P>
The Nations Cup is the second of six competitions in the
Championships series, which end in Munich from December 19 to 21,
the last major international competition before the 1998 Winter
Olympics in Nagano, Japan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
