<HEADLINE> Chinese Taipei Big Winners at Disabled Table Tennis Tourney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Taipei team became
the top winners with a impressive, top-ranked collection of 16
medals as the inaugural Far East and South Pacific Table Tennis
Championships for the Disabled closed here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Players from Chinese Taipei won four gold, seven silver and
five bronze medals to top the teams medal table.
</P>
<P>
Japan was second on the medal tally with four golds, five
silvers and four bronzes and South Korea finished third with a
medal credit of 4-1-8.
</P>
<P>
From fourth to sixth were Hong Kong, China, China and Thailand,
with medal collections of 3-3-6, 3-2-4 and 0-0-1 respectively.
</P>
<P>
The four-day event, with a participation of 105 players from 10
countries and regions, was the first event ever held in the region
to offer world ranking points to the participants.
</P>
<P>
The championships were jointly organized by the Hong Kong
Sports Association for the Physically Disabled and the Provincial
Urban Council, with financial support from the Hong Kong Sports
Development Board. 
</P>
</TEXT>
