<HEADLINE> Clavet, Lapentti Enter Colombian Open Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, Colombia, November 1 (Xinhua) -- Top-seeded Francisco
Clavet of Spain and 1995 titlist Nicholas Lapentti of Ecuador
entered the final of the Colombian Open tennis tournament on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Clavet needed three sets to beat his Italian rival Davide
Sanguinetti 6-3, 6-7 (4-7), 7-6 (7-3) on Saturday to advance to
the final.
</P>
<P>
Lapentti, who won the tournament as a qualifier in 1995, scored
a straight-set victory of 6-2, 7-5 over Vincent Spadea to set up
the final clash with Clavet. 
