<HEADLINE> Brodie Takes Commonwealth Super-bantamweight Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, November 1 (Xinhua) -- Michael Brodie of Britain
claimed the Commonwealth super-bantamweight title by defeating
Wilson Docherty of Scotland with a fourth-round knockout in
Glasgow, Scotland on Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
Brodie finished the bout with body punches as Docherty was
stopped inside the distance for the first time in his career.
</P>
<P>
Brodie made his record to 21-0.
</P>
<P>
South African Johnson Tshuma won the vacant Commonwealth
light-middleweight title with a 12-round points win over Paul
Jones of Britain in London on Friday night. Tshuma improved his
record to 20-2. 
</P>
