<HEADLINE> Clinton Vetoes Energy, NASA Spending Bills </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, November 1 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton
today used line-item power to veto 10 government projects
involving 20 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Projects include a cemetery for veterans, a solar energy
demonstration project and a NASA telescope. The White House said
seven were cut from a 69 billion dollars measure financing
veterans, housing, environmental and other programs. The other
three were tweezed out of a 42 billion dollars transportation
bill.
</P>
<P>
Prior to this, Clinton had cast 63 line-item vetoes on six
previous bills, mostly cutting defense programs and military
construction projects.
</P>
<P>
The vetoes would reduce 1.9 billion dollars of spending over
the next five years. Clinton said the projects were duplicated
other government projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
